This paper involves the use of deep learning algorithms for crime classification and prediction, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with crime data and its analysis, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper also involves the use of open data and data analysis, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
